Description: CVE-2026-44169 - SHOW CREATE ROUTINE role privilege check (MDEV-39288)
 Upstream fix f279551013d1319f27344080e2c0758f3959cebf targets MariaDB 11.4
 where MDEV-29167 had refactored check_routine_level_acl() to take a
 privilege_t acl parameter; the role-branch incorrectly compared against
 SHOW_PROC_WITHOUT_DEFINITION_ACLS, masking SHOW CREATE PROCEDURE for users
 whose access comes from a granted role.
 .
 MariaDB 10.11.14 (this target) does NOT contain MDEV-29167. Its
 check_routine_level_acl() in sql/sql_acl.cc has no acl parameter, has no
 SHOW_PROC_WITHOUT_DEFINITION_ACLS symbol, and already uses SHOW_PROC_ACLS
 in BOTH the user-grant branch and the role-grant branch. That is exactly
 the post-fix semantic of the upstream patch, so 10.11 is not affected by
 this CVE on the source-code side.
 .
 To lock in this not-affected status and guard against future regressions,
 this patch back-ports only the upstream regression test (mysql-test/main/
 sp-security.{test,result}). The 11.x-only @save_sql_mode and conn1 hunks
 are dropped because the surrounding context does not exist in 10.11. The
 MDEV-39288 test block is appended after 10.11's existing
 "# End of 10.6 tests" marker rather than the 11.4 marker.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/MariaDB/server/commit/f279551013d1319f27344080e2c0758f3959cebf
Bug: https://jira.mariadb.org/browse/MDEV-39288
Bug-Debian: https://github.com/MariaDB/server/security/advisories/GHSA-22xq-vq3f-87x2
Author: Sergei Golubchik <serg@mariadb.org>
Last-Update: 2026-07-21

--- a/mysql-test/main/sp-security.test
+++ b/mysql-test/main/sp-security.test
@@ -1123,3 +1123,26 @@ drop function f;
 --echo #
 --echo # End of 10.6 tests
 --echo #
+
+--echo #
+--echo # MDEV-39288 SHOW CREATE ROUTINE does not apply to roles
+--echo #
+create user u@localhost;
+create role r;
+create procedure p1() select 10 as ten;
+grant execute on procedure test.p1 to u@localhost;
+grant execute on procedure test.p1 to r;
+grant r to u@localhost;
+
+connect u, localhost, u;
+call p1();
+query_vertical show create procedure p1;
+set role r;
+query_vertical Show create procedure p1;
+disconnect u;
+
+connection default;
+drop role r;
+drop user u@localhost;
+drop procedure p1;
+
